{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The wedge.} Three structural openings:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b EU/Saudi data residency concerns} \u8212- same theme as plan 01's GoHighLevel pitch, but here the regulator is NCA / SDAIA in Saudi and TDRA in UAE. Self-hosted on Tier-3 datacentre {\b inside the country} (e.g., Khazna, STC, G42) is increasingly required for tourism / wellness data tied to government programs.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Arabic + RTL is uneven across competitors.} Cloudbeds Arabic UI is partial. Most local agencies build Arabic frontends manually. A polished VBWD Arabic + RTL package becomes a real differentiator.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Halal-tourism / Umrah-package operators} are underserved by Western SaaS. They want package builder, voucher delivery, group bookings, prayer-time integrations \u8212- niche but profitable.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Local payment rails\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Stripe} \u8212- live in both UAE and KSA (Stripe MENA launched 2024)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Mada} (Saudi national debit network) \u8212- handled via Hyperpay, Checkout.com, PayTabs, Network International\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Tabby, Tamara} (BNPL, dominant in GCC e-commerce)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Apple Pay, Google Pay} (very high penetration in UAE/KSA)\par}
